# Secrets — `.env` may carry live Supabase/Apps Script credentials and
# must NEVER be committed. Use `.env.local` (or proper secret management)
# for real values; `.env.example` is the only env file that should be
# tracked, and it must hold only placeholders.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

